summary:
The Security Council,

Recalling resolutions on Yemen and the Red Sea, including 2216 (2015) and 2722 (2024),

Condemns Houthi attacks on merchant and commercial vessels,

Reaffirms respect for Red Sea coastal States' sovereignty and territorial integrity,

1. Extends reporting request until January 15, 2025;
2. Demands Houthis cease attacks, release M/V Galaxy Leader and its crew;
3. Emphasizes addressing root causes, including conflicts and regional tensions, and adherence to targeted arms embargo;
4. Urges caution, restraint, and diplomatic efforts to avoid escalation;
5. Decides to remain seized of this matter.
